{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-set-up-smtp-email-for-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to set up SMTP Email for Magento 2","content":"\n<p>May every online merchant be familiar with sending systems. In this post, we provide a general guideline on<strong><em> How to set up SMTP Email for Magento 2</em></strong> stores. If you&#8217;re wondering about the default SMTP settings in Magento 2, it&#8217;s important to note that the platform is designed to work with a wide range of online mail servers and providers. <strong><em>What is the default SMTP settings in Magento 2</em></strong> is a common question among users, as the configuration for the default email mode in Magento 2 can be complicated for new users. However, this guide aims to give you a deeper understanding of <strong><em>Magento 2 SMTP settings</em></strong>. SMTP, or Simple Mail Transfer Protocol, is a standard email-sending system first introduced in the late 20th century. By default, Magento 2 uses its built-in SMTP functionality to send online mail, but as mentioned earlier, this may not always be effective in ensuring that your emails reach your customers&#8217; inboxes. Configuring SMTP Email using the <strong><em>how to set up SMTP email for Magento 2</em></strong> guidelines is a great way to improve the deliverability of your emails and maximize the effectiveness of your online mail marketing efforts.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3 Steps Guide: How to Set Up SMTP Email for Magento 2</h1>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Obtain a Valid Email Address</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re wondering about the default Simple Mail Transfer Protocol settings in Magento 2, it&#8217;s important to note that the platform is designed to work with a wide range of email servers and providers. However, the default SMTP settings may not always be effective in ensuring that your online emails reach your customers&#8217; inboxes. This is where Magento 2 SMTP settings come into play. By configuring SMTP online mail for your Magento 2 store using the <strong><em>how to set up SMTP email for Magento 2</em></strong> guidelines, you can improve the deliverability of your online mail and prevent them from being sent to spam or outbox folders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, you&#8217;ll need to obtain a valid online mail address for your domain by following the guidelines provided by your server administrator or email hosting provider. This step is also known as SMTP Email setting for Magento 2. Once you have a valid email address, you can proceed with configuring an SMTP email using the steps provided by the SMTP extension or other available resources. Properly setting up SMTP emails is crucial for ensuring that your emails are being delivered to your customers&#8217; inboxes and maximizing the effectiveness of your email marketing efforts.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Configure Email Sending for Magento Stores</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To configure email sending for your Magento store, follow these steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1154 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:1024px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;387&#x27;%20width=&#x27;1024&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transf